descript.abstract: This dataset is a polygon representation of the parcels for the Town of Cohasset, Massachusetts. Edits to a base parcel file were made to the spatial and tabular data in order to bring the file in compliance with November 2010 MassGIS Level III Standards for Digital Parcel Files. These edits included ensuring that the parcel fabric was continuous and closed with no gaps or overlaps. Additionally, parcels were snapped to the legislatively approved MassGIS TOWNSSURVEY_ARC town boundary datalayer and compared against the 2008 30 cm MassGIS Ortho Imagery. Polygons were assigned a LOC_ID that links to the M065Assessor table and other fields were populated where they were known and applicable.
descript.purpose: The purpose of this dataset is to provide the Massachuesetts Office of Geographic Information with a polygon representation of the parcels for the Town of Cohasset, Massachuesetts that comply with its Level III standards.

dataqual.logic: This parcel layer contains discrete, non-overlapping polygons for each property. Adjacent polygons with common ownership and a single tax record have been retained in the "OthLeg" layer that accompanies this TaxPar layer, and dissolved into single parcels in this TaxPar layer. Some non-adjacent parcels may be represented by multi-part polygons where they share common ownership and a single tax record. Public right of ways exist as polygons, not null space. Linework associated with private ROWs are retained in the "OthLeg" layer. Water polygons also representing parcel boundaries have been retained in this TaxPar layer. Additional water features that are not considered parcel boundaries may have been placed in the "Misc" layer that accompanies this TaxPar layer. Easements and other similar non-fee taxable boundaries exist in the 'OthLeg" layer, not the TaxPar layer.

attracc.attraccr: Required match rate for 3110 parcels: 99.0 pct Total number of parcels with "TAX" or "FEE" POLY_TYPE = 3103 Of these, 3043 join to assessor list. Match rate for "FEE"/"TAX" parcels to assessor table: 98.1 pct **** Parcel to assessor match rate is below spec. Does not pass QA.

horizpa.horizpar: Data compiled or reviewed for horizontal accuracy ove the MassGIS color orthos from 2008/2009; these orthos are known to be +/- 10' horizontal; however, this data set cannot be used to reach authoritative conclusions about the horizontal accuracy of the boundaries depicted. That work requires a licensed land surveyor.

srcinfo.srccontr: Scanned copies of Cohasset's Original Assessor maps produced by Hartley L. White in the early 20th century were provided by Weston Graphics in Hinngham, MA. These maps were produeced at a 1 inch = 80 feet scale and used to verify the boundaries of the GIS parcels.

procstep.procdesc: MassGIS gathered the base GIS parcel data from the Town of Cohasset and conducted a preliminary data review. This included matching CAMA records to the GIS parcels, consolidating "TAX" parcels, and transerfing appropriate "FEE" parcels to the M065OthLeg dataset.

Parcels boundaries were visually verified against base map features in the 2008/2009 30cm USGS Color Ortho Imagery. Visual inconsistencies between the parcels and imagery of greater than 3m were fixed when such changes were supported by parcel boundaries as shown in the original assessor maps.

Parcel polygons were adjusted to the MassGIS TOWNSURVEY_ARC polyline along boundaries with other towns. There is a known border discrepancy between Cohasset and Scituate. In this area, parcels have been created to fill the gap between Cohasset's mapping of parcels and the Scitaute border. The tax records and parcel boundaries within this gap have been retained in Scituate's digital parcel data.
Topology rule checks were performed to remove slivers and gaps between taxable parcels.

Tax parcel data checked against CAMA data to identify parcel data missing assessor record information. Discrepancies were addressed through consultation with individual communities and referencing assessor maps and records.

overview.dsoverv: This dataset is a polygon representation of the parcels for the Town of Cohasset, Massachusetts. MassGIS gathered the digital parcel information for this community and conduted a preliminary data review. The data was then passed on to Coler and Colantonio, Inc to bring the data in compliance with with the November 2010 MassGIS Level III Standards for Digital Parcel Files. Much of the alterations to the data were made to align parcel boundaries to be within 3m of the 2008 30 cm MassGIS Ortho Imagery. These edits were made where they were supported by georefenced copies of Cohasset's original Assessor Maps, provided by Weston Graphics in Hingham, MA. Edits we also made to ensure the parcel fabric was continuous and closed with no gaps or overlaps. Additionally, parcels were snapped to the legislatively approved MassGIS TOWNSSURVEY_ARC town boundary datalayer. Polygons were assigned a LOC_ID that links to the M065Assessor table and other fields were populated where they were known and applicable.
